class Solution {
    public boolean isPalindrome(int x) {
        String[] num = String.valueOf(x).split("");

        for (int i = 0; i < num.length / 2; i++) {
            if (!num[i].equals(num[num.length - 1 - i])) {
                return false;
            }
        }

        return true;
    }
}
â€œTo check if a string is a valid palindrome, I use a two-pointer approach.
I set one pointer at the start (left) and one at the end (right).
While left < right, I skip any characters that are not letters or digits.
Then I compare the lowercase versions of s[left] and s[right].
If theyâ€™re not equal, I return false.
If they match, I move the left pointer forward and the right pointer backward.
If the loop finishes without finding a mismatch, the string is a palindrome.â€

